text: Zapata County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. It was founded in 1858. In 2020, 13,889 people lived there. Its county seat is Zapata. == History == Zapata County was founded in 1858. == Geography == The county has a total area of 1,058 square miles (2,740 kmÂ²). == Places == * Falcon Lake Estates * Zapata (county seat) ==References== Category:Texas counties Category:1858 establishments in the United States Category:1850s establishments in Texas
